article.description: — Daniss Jenkins scored 23 points as St. John's beat Georgetown 86-78 on Saturday.
article.headline: Jenkins scores 23, St. John's knocks off Georgetown 86-78
article.linkText: Jenkins scores 23, St. John's knocks off Georgetown 86-78
article.story: NEW YORK -- — Daniss Jenkins scored 23 points as St. John's beat Georgetown 86-78 on Saturday. Jenkins added seven assists for the Red Storm (19-12, 11-9 Big East Conference). RJ Luis added 16 points while going 6 of 8 and 4 of 6 from the free-throw line while he also had three steals. Chris Ledlum went 6 of 6 from the field to finish with 14 points. Jayden Epps led the way for the Hoyas (9-22, 2-18) with 23 points and six steals. Jay Heath added 14 points for Georgetown. Drew Fielder also had 12 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
